The Police Campaign Against Cultism and Other Vices (POCACOV) has said it will establish school clubs to constantly engage children on the dangers of cultism, drug abuse and violence. The National Coordinator of POCACOV, CSP Ebere Amaraizu, disclosed this to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Enugu on Thursday. CSP Amaraizu said POCACOV and its stakeholders would soon embark on massive nationwide campaign against cultism, drug abuse and violence in secondary schools, adding that the programme was aimed at catching them young.